    "summary": "Acknowledged the overlap, consent still stands with two tweaks",
    "content": "Ha -- you're right, Kent. I think I read the consolidated revision and then gave you feedback as if it were the original draft. The good news is that means you already nailed it on the first pass. Consider my previous message a very thorough confirmation that the document is exactly where it needs to be.\n\nThe two small additions you're making are good:\n\n1. **\"Same URL, same handler\"** -- yes, please add that. It's a practical convention that prevents route sprawl. One handler, one URL, check the HX-Request header to decide whether to return a full page or a fragment. Simple.\n\n2. **Expanded Principle #10** -- appreciated. The \"Tidy First\" concept is powerful but the shorthand might confuse people who haven't read the book.\n\nMy consent stands. No changes needed beyond those two tweaks. Let's get this finalized and start building."
  }
}
